Sequence Information.Peptide Name: CATHPb2 (natural AMPs; cathelicidins; snake, reptiles, animals; UCLL1)

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that the sequence of the peptide shows 37% similarity toWAM1. molecular formula: C155H252N50O33S1; Mol Wt: 3389.072; GRAVY = -0.6.Activity: Active against Gram+ S. aureus ATCC25923 or MRSA (MIC 75 ug/mL or greater), S. epidermidis (MIC 75 ug/mL), N. asteroids (MIC 37.5 ug/ml), B. cereus (MIC 9.38 ug/ml), E.faecalis IS 981 (MIC >100 ug/mL), E. faecium IS 1299 (MIC 18.75 ug/mL), Gram- E. coli ATCC25922 (MIC 37.5-75 ug/ml), K.oxytoca (MIC >100 ug/ml) , S. paratyphi IS 738 (MIC 75 ug/ml), D. bacillus (MIC 2.34 ug/ml), K. pneumoniae (MIC 75 ug/ml or more), S. maltophilia (MIC 9.38 ug/ml), P.aeruginosa ATCC 27853 (MIC>100 ug/ml), and fungi C. albicans (MIC 18.75-37.5 ug/mL) and C. glabrata (MIC 37.5-75 ug/ml).Toxicity:  hRBC: 7.28% at 100 ug/ml. poor hemo.lytic.
